This paper deals with learning to describe fine-grained visual differences between instances using attribute phrases, which involves computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The paper also presents a framework for a reference game between a speaker and a listener, which involves machine learning (cs.AI) and reinforcement learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of attribute-based representations for image retrieval, which involves information retrieval (cs.IR).
